Back in the day in Bulgaria if you worked a factory or mining type job where you were exposed to a heavily toxic environment you legally had to receive free yogurt from the job place as an antitoxin detox type thing. Gypsies refused to work any job with "free yogurt" out of fear.

You went to do your job at the agricultural chemical facility or whatever and had to breathe in fumes for a few hours. Coughing up particles on your break. You got a free cup of yogurt from the state as to keep you alive another day. Meditate on this image under a cold waterfall.

Old people here in Bulgaria also think back fondly of e.g. being able to get bananas or other exotic fruits around New Year and having to wait for hours on long queues for them, being able to afford cheap sweets when they were schoolchildren, etc. Poverty, youth, food

I wish Dr. Hans Selye wrote newsletters similar to Peat but I guess he was too busy running rat experiments 24/7. The "newsletter" seems to me one of the most conductive textual forms for transmitting scientific ideas, including the old school health newspapers in Eastern Europe.

Dr. Hans Selye said the future of medical science was treating disease by strengthening the immune system by "artificial hibernation" induced by ataraxic drugs and hormones. He himself discovered super high dose progesterone knocks anyone out unconscious so he was thinking of it.

Reading insider tobacco industry documents on smoking and Dr. Hans Selye and it's just him talking about how if you don't drive cars fast or smoke enough you will die of a heart attack or get a stroke
Getting called into the human resources office because a coworker accused you of being brown

He uses the example of bleeding because both his father and grandfather, medical doctors, were still practicing it when he was himself a child, bleeding patients by opening their veins with knives and stuff

Hans Selye literally invented stress as a concept but then ironically enough basically killed himself by working 14 hours a day for five decades in a row and waking up 4 AM every morning. When people teased him about it he said the inventor of the race car is not the best driver.

Preg/P5, DHEA, Norboletone, Spironolactone, Methandriol, Methyltestosterone, Nandrolone, Ethylestrenol, Norethandrolone and some other steroids are all listed by Selye as "catatoxic steroids" that prevent poisoning with various drugs. Classification that no one talks about now.

I get why Ray Peat called Hans Selye a conservative now. Basically all of the things he's trying to do is just limiting stress, stopping catabolism, neutralizing poisons. He's always on the defensive. It's basically Tigran Petrosian's chess style applied to biology and medicine.

Selye was actually using a form called pregnenolone-16α-carbonitrile in some experiments but Haidut/Georgi Dinkov believes it's the same thing, if it's taken orally Pregnenolone keeps cycling and getting absorbed from the intestine for like a week from a single dose anyways iirc.
